cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about image deconvolution using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a Recurrent Gradient Descent Network (RGDN) that incorporates deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves optimization techniques, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on synthetic benchmarks and real-world images, which could indicate that it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia).
